sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Ingress as Platform Ingress<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant API as vLLM API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Runner as HPU Model Runner<br/>(in-process)
    participant HPU as Gaudi HPU Device<br/>(HPU DMA)
    participant Peer as HPU Workers<br/>(TP rank 1..N)
    participant NIXL_A as NIXL Buffer<br/>(Node A)
    participant NIXL_B as NIXL Buffer<br/>(Node B)
    participant Storage as Model Storage<br/>(PVC/S3)

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 1: Model Inference Request

    Client->>Ingress: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (platform SSO)
    Ingress->>API: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8000 (cluster-internal, plaintext)
    API->>Runner: Python function call<br/>(in-process)

    Note over Runner: Bucketing: quantize input dims<br/>to pre-compiled graph shapes

    Runner->>HPU: Execute model forward pass<br/>habana_frameworks API (HPU DMA)

    Note over HPU: Attention backend selected:<br/>Standard / MLA / Unified / UnifiedMLA

    alt Tensor Parallel (multi-card)
        HPU->>Peer: HCCL all-reduce / all-gather<br/>RDMA/TCP (Dynamic port, No encryption)
        Peer-->>HPU: Collective result
    end

    HPU-->>Runner: Inference result
    Runner-->>API: Generated tokens
    API-->>Ingress: JSON response<br/>HTTP/8000
    Ingress-->>Client: Response<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+

    Note over NIXL_A,NIXL_B: Flow 2: Multi-Node KV Cache Transfer (NIXL)

    Runner->>NIXL_A: Memory copy to host<br/>transfer buffer (CPU)
    NIXL_A->>NIXL_B: NIXL transfer<br/>RDMA/TCP (Dynamic port, No encryption)
    NIXL_B->>Runner: Memory copy from<br/>host buffer to HPU

    Note over Runner,Storage: Flow 3: Model Loading (startup)

    Runner->>Storage: Load model weights<br/>(PVC mount or HTTPS/443 to S3)
    Storage-->>Runner: Model artifacts<br/>(safetensors / bin)

    Note over Runner,HPU: Flow 4: FP8 Calibration (offline)

    Runner->>HPU: Calibration forward passes<br/>habana_frameworks API
    HPU-->>Runner: Measurement data<br/>(activation/weight statistics)
    Runner->>Runner: Compute FP8 scales<br/>(INC quantization)
    Runner->>Storage: Save quantized scales<br/>to model artifacts (File I/O)
